name: darkblue94/recipe-app
description: I created a web-app with React that makes API calls to "food2fork.com" , reviving an object that contains Recipes Names , Links, Publishers and Images. I target my input element of 'name' and pass its value into a const variable which I  concatenate in the url that is being fetched. I take all that data into my state, pass it as a prop in my Recipes component and I use the map function to unbox every instance of a recipe that contains the main ingredient searched by the user.

name: darkblue94/react-step-form
description: Here I create a fluid , step form with React. A step form is a form broken down into steps. Here I create a step for "FirstName,LastName,Email", a second step for "Instrument,City,Bio", a third step for a chance for the user to review and confirm the date the put into the form. I use State and props to keep track of the step I was in(0-4). With functions like nextStep and prevStep I was able to add or take away form state.step. The value of Step determines what I Component I have UserForm return.
